E","active_lock_reason":null,"body":"Thanks for adding the MLFlow pipelines feature to your API!\r\n\r\nOur situation is as follows:\r\n\r\n- We want to share steps between train and inference pipelines\r\n- To do this, we would need to be able to create multiple pipelines in a single directory\r\n- However, we see [here](https://github.com/mlflow/mlflow/blob/0ab45a6e11f17484589a6195bd1fccb2e0a3c389/mlflow/pipelines/utils/__init__.py#L11) that the pipeline name is hard-coded. \r\n\r\nIs there a specific reason why we cannot simply pass the name of the pipeline ('pipeline_train.yaml', 'pipeline_inference.yaml') to the `Pipeline` mlflow class? How otherwise would you propose that users share steps between their pipelines?\r\n\r\nWe understand that this is an experimental feature. Happy to make a PR to propose implementing the above.","closed_by":null,"reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/mlflow/mlflow/issues/6209/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/mlflow/mlflow/issues/6209/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":null}